Bridge design pattern: It  decouples an abstraction from its implementation using composition, allowing both to vary independently and preventing class explosion from inheritance combinations.

JdbsTemplate + DataSources: JdbcTemplate (abstraction) works with any DataSource (HikariCP, DBCP, DriverManager) implementation. Switch connection pools without changing DAO code.

MessageSenders: Spring abstractions like SimpleMailMessage use Email, SMS, or Slack sender implementations interchangeably.


Java Implementation: Video Encoder Example

Step 1: Implementor interface (implementation hierarchy).
interface VideoEncoder {
    void encode(String filename);
}

Step 2: Concrete implementors.
class MPEGEncoder implements VideoEncoder {
    public void encode(String filename) {
        System.out.println("Encoding " + filename + " to MPEG format");
    }
}
class VP8Encoder implements VideoEncoder {
    public void encode(String filename) {
        System.out.println("Encoding " + filename + " to VP8 format");
    }
}

Step 3: Abstraction with implementor reference.
abstract class VideoTranscoder {
    protected VideoEncoder encoder;

    public VideoTranscoder(VideoEncoder encoder) {
        this.encoder = encoder;
    }
}

Step 4: Refined abstractions (abstraction hierarchy).
class HighQualityTranscoder extends VideoTranscoder {
    public HighQualityTranscoder(VideoEncoder encoder) {
        super(encoder);
    }

    public void transcode(String filename) {
        System.out.print("High quality ");
        encoder.encode(filename);
    }
}
class LowQualityTranscoder extends VideoTranscoder {
    public LowQualityTranscoder(VideoEncoder encoder) {
        super(encoder);
    }

    public void transcode(String filename) {
        System.out.print("Low quality ");
        encoder.encode(filename);
    }
}

Step 5: Client usage - mix and match independently.
public class BridgeDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // 4 combinations without 4 classes!
        VideoTranscoder t1 = new HighQualityTranscoder(new MPEGEncoder());
        t1.transcode("video1.mp4");  // High quality Encoding video1.mp4 to MPEG format

        VideoTranscoder t2 = new LowQualityTranscoder(new VP8Encoder());
        t2.transcode("video2.mp4");  // Low quality Encoding video2.mp4 to VP8 format
    }
}

*** This scales to N abstractions × M implementations = NM combinations without subclass explosion.